President Obama released a statement on Yom Kippur, extending wishes for an easy fast to those observing the Day of Atonement. He emphasized that Yom Kippur is a time for humility, reflection, and repentance, urging individuals and communities to be honest about their shortcomings. The President also highlighted the hope that comes with Yom Kippur, stating that through prayers and actions, we can bridge the gap between the realities of our world and the shared ideals and values. He concluded by expressing his hope for our common humanity to unite us and inspire us to continue healing the world.